METROPOLITAN STEAM LAUNDRY CO., Respondent, v. CHATFIELD, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. March 1, 1894.) Appeal from sixth district court. Action by the Metropolitan Steam Laundry Company against John Chat-field.

Argued before BISOHOPP and GIEGERICH, JJ.

P. A. Wilcox, for appellant. C. D. Rust, for. respondent.

No opinion. Judgment reversed, new trial ordered, with costs to abide the event.
